ğŸ§© Problem Statement
Students often struggle to find internships, scholarships, hackathons, and learning opportunities because information is scattered across multiple websites, WhatsApp groups, and social media platforms.
As a result, many students miss deadlines and face confusion while searching for genuine opportunities.


ğŸ’¡ Our Solution
Student Opportunity Hub is a centralized web platform designed to bring all important student opportunities into one simple and easy-to-use website.
The goal is to help students discover opportunities quickly without confusion or information overload.


ğŸš€ Features Implemented

ğŸ”¹ Round 1
Centralized listing of internships, scholarships, hackathons, and courses
Category-based browsing
Clean and student-friendly interface
Basic project prototype

ğŸ”¹ Round 2 Enhancements
Fully designed and responsive homepage
Dedicated opportunities page
Working apply buttons and navigation
Improved UI/UX using CSS
JavaScript-based frontend interactivity
Proper system design documentation (DFD, DB Schema, SQL)


ğŸ”„ How the Website Works (User Flow)
Student opens the website
Homepage introduces the platform
Student navigates to the opportunities section
Available opportunities are displayed clearly
Student clicks on an opportunity
Student applies using the provided apply button or link


ğŸ“Š Data Flow (Simple Explanation)
Opportunity data is currently handled as static data
User actions such as clicks and navigation are managed through JavaScript
The frontend displays opportunities in a structured and readable format


ğŸ“ Documentation (Docs Folder)
The Docs folder contains all supporting documents related to the project, including:
Data Flow Diagram (DFD)
Database Schema Diagram
SQL database design
These documents explain the system flow, data structure, and backend planning of the project.


ğŸ§  Backend Explanation (Planned Architecture)
This project is currently implemented as a working frontend prototype. Backend development has been planned and designed, but not implemented in this round due to time constraints.
Backend logic is defined using DFD and DB Schema
SQL scripts describe database tables and relationships
The system is backend-ready and scalable
Backend technologies like Node.js, Express, and MySQL can be integrated in future phases


